  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Au Gratin Potatoes': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The pepper cuts gruyere-cream richness and the medium body handles dairy weight. Works for au gratin — Muga Reserva\'s vanilla-leather plays with the cheese harder.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Brussels and Belly': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The pepper cuts pork-belly fat and the garrigue echoes brussels-char. Strong Southern-French for brussels-and-belly — Rhône savory polish on a fat-and-char side.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Burrata': 'Never pair Kermit Lynch Rhône with burrata — garrigue and pepper clash with fresh cream and the wild herbs fight tomato-basil brightness. Lead with Santa Margherita Pinot Grigio\'s clean lift or a Rosé\'s strawberry-to-tomato-sweetness bridge.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Cowboy Ribeye': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The medium body is slightly light for Cowboy\'s marbled 22oz bone-in ribeye, but the pepper matches grilled char. Works for ribeye — Grand Tinel\'s Châteauneuf full-body handles the cut harder.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Crab Cake': 'Never pair Kermit Lynch Rhône with crab cake — wild herbs and pepper overwhelm delicate lump crab and the garrigue bury the remoulade. Lead with Heitz Sauvignon Blanc\'s citrus lift or Reverdy Sancerre\'s mineral edge for shellfish clarity.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Creamed Spinach': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The medium body handles dairy-heavy cream and the wild herbs lift spinach-iron. Strong Southern-French for creamed spinach — a gentle Rhône counterpoint to the rich side.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Faroe Island Salmon': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The medium body handles salmon\'s oil-richness and the red cherry lifts against flesh-sweetness. Peak Southern-French for salmon — preparation changes seasonally, check with kitchen for today\'s build.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Filet Mignon': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The medium body matches butter-tender filet\'s delicate weight and the wild herbs play against escargot-butter. Strong Southern-French for filet — a lighter-touch Rhône pairing.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|G.D. Vajra Moscato d\'Asti': 'Never pour Kermit Lynch Rhône in a Moscato flight — a dry, savory Southern-French red inside a sweet low-alcohol sparkling flight collapses the flight\'s logic. Pour each at its own course. For a peppery-red flight, sequence through Rhône-Malbec-Châteauneuf instead.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Grilled Caesar': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The wild herbs match anchovy-lemon dressing and the pepper cuts through parm. Peak Southern-French for grilled caesar — Kermit Lynch food-wine handles the salad beautifully.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|House Wedge': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The garrigue plays with blue-cheese funk and the pepper matches bacon-fat char. Strong Southern-French for wedge — medium body handles iceberg-cold without muting.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Kansas City': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The pepper note echoes Kansas City\'s lean-bold beef char and the wild herbs lift against grilled strip. Peak Southern-French for the strip — a mid-weight garrigue match.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Mushrooms': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The garrigue savory-finish echoes roasted-mushroom glutamate and the pepper note plays with butter. Peak Southern-French for mushrooms — Rhône garrigue-on-earth match.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Porterhouse': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. Medium body is slightly light for Porterhouse\'s dual-cut heft, but wild herbs play against grilled beef. Works for Porterhouse — Tempier Bandol or Scavino Barolo handles the cut harder.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Roast Half Chicken': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch selection, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body, food-friendly. The wild herbs echo chicken-jus herbaceousness and medium body won\'t overwhelm poultry. Peak Southern-French for the bird — preparation changes seasonally, check with kitchen for today\'s build.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Sauteed Garlic Spinach': 'Rhône Valley Côtes du Rhône Grenache-Syrah-Mourvèdre — Kermit Lynch, red cherry, wild herbs, pepper, garrigue, medium body. The wild herbs echo garlic-oil aromatics and the medium body matches spinach-iron. Strong Southern-French for garlic spinach — Rhône herb-on-herb harmony.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Seared Scallops': 'Never pair Kermit Lynch Rhône with seared scallops — pepper and garrigue overwhelm delicate sweet shellfish and the medium body clashes with browned-butter. Lead with Clos de la Chapelle Chardonnay or Rombauer\'s creamy richness for sear-seared harmony.',
  'Kermit Lynch Côtes du Rhône|Shrimp Cocktail': 'Never pair Kermit Lynch Rhône with shrimp cocktail — cold shrimp plus cocktail-sauce horseradish gets crushed by pepper and garrigue, and the red-fruit has nowhere to land. Lead with Laurent Perrier Brut Champagne\'s bubble-driven palate reset.',
  'Lail Vineyards Blueprint|Au Gratin Potatoes': 'Napa Cab — Lail entry-level, polished blackcurrant, cedar, dark cherry, refined medium tannin. The refined tannin cuts gruyère-cream weight and the cedar plays against the lactic richness. Works as historically-pedigreed Napa Cab for au gratin — Lail family polish on the cheesy side.',
