  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Beignets': 'Tours-sur-Marne Pinot Noir rosé Champagne — silky mousse, red berry, long finish. The strawberry-raspberry complements beignets\' berry-jam filling directly and bubbles cut fried-dough weight. Strong Champagne-and-beignets pairing — the dessert mirrors the berry profile of the rosé.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Bone Marrow': 'Pinot Noir rosé Champagne against marrow\'s rendered-fat richness — the silky strawberry profile is crushed by bone depth. Never pair. Route marrow to big Cab, Manhattan, or Bowdie\'s Old Fashioned and save the rosé for the raw bar or tartare opener.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Burrata': 'Pinot Noir Champagne rosé — silky mousse, red berry aromas, long elegant finish. The strawberry-raspberry cuts burrata\'s cream and plays cleanly against basil-tomato-pistachio. Peak rosé Champagne for burrata — the berry-fruit framework meets the salad\'s delicate build beautifully.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Caymus Cabernet Sauvignon': 'Benchmark silky Pinot Noir rosé Champagne alongside Napa Cab\'s cocoa-mocha-tannin weight — zero structural overlap. Never layer. Route Caymus to the steak course and keep Laurent Perrier rosé for the opener or between-course celebration pour — both deserve their moment.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Cowboy Ribeye': 'Pinot Noir rosé Champagne against the Cowboy\'s marbled bone-in ribeye — the berry-led mousse has no weight to meet rendered fat and char. Never pair. Route Cowboy to Silver Oak, Caymus, or bold bourbon and keep the rosé for the opener or raw bar.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Crab Cake': 'Tours-sur-Marne Pinot Noir rosé Champagne — benchmark rosé with red berry aromas, silky mousse, long elegant finish. The berry fruit cuts crab\'s sweet remoulade and bubbles lift the cake\'s pan-fry. Peak rosé Champagne for crab cake — sophisticated starter pour at benchmark quality.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Escargot': 'Pinot Noir Champagne rosé — silky red-berry mousse with a long elegant finish. The fine bubbles and structured body cut escargot\'s garlic-parsley butter weight, and the berry profile plays against the rich snail texture. Strong benchmark Champagne choice for escargot.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Faroe Island Salmon': 'Pinot Noir Champagne rosé — silky mousse, red berry aromas, long elegant finish. The structure and body handle salmon\'s oil-rich flesh; preparation changes seasonally — check with kitchen for today\'s build. Works well as rosé Champagne across most seasonal salmon preparations.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Filet Mignon': 'Pinot Noir Champagne rosé — silky structured mousse, red berry complexity, long elegant finish. The body and berry frame handle butter-tender filet\'s lean sweetness unconventionally, and bubbles lift the sear. Strong alternative when guest wants Champagne with their steak instead of classic Cab.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Grilled Caesar': 'Pinot Noir Champagne rosé — benchmark silky mousse, red berry notes, long elegant finish. The bubbles cut anchovy-parmesan dressing and the structure meets grilled-romaine char; strawberry adds lift against the heavy salad. Strong rosé Champagne pour for grilled Caesar.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|House Wedge': 'Tours-sur-Marne Pinot Noir rosé — benchmark Champagne with strawberry, raspberry, silky mousse, long finish. The red berry cuts iceberg-and-bacon and the structure meets blue cheese dressing without crumpling. Strong elegant pairing for wedge — sophisticated opener that reframes the classic.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Prime Tartare': 'Pinot Noir Champagne rosé from Tours-sur-Marne — benchmark rosé with silky structured mousse, strawberry, raspberry, fresh cherry, and long elegant finish. The red-berry complexity meets raw prime beef\'s iron richness directly and the silky mousse holds through each bite. Peak rosé Champagne for tartare.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Roast Half Chicken': 'Pinot Noir rosé Champagne from Tours-sur-Marne — silky mousse, red berry, elegant finish. The body and berry frame can handle roasted chicken; preparation changes seasonally — check with kitchen for today\'s build. Works as sophisticated Champagne pairing for the chicken course.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Scavino Barolo': 'Silky Pinot Noir rosé Champagne against Piedmont Nebbiolo\'s tar-and-tannin intensity — Barolo\'s structure obliterates the delicate rosé mousse. Never layer. Route Barolo to the Tomahawk or Porterhouse course and keep the LP rosé for raw bar, tartare, or the opener.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Seafood Tower': 'Pinot Noir Champagne rosé — silky structured mousse with strawberry, raspberry, and fresh cherry. The fine bubbles and red-berry complexity reset the palate between oysters, shrimp, and crab and elevate the whole shellfish platter. Peak sophisticated rosé Champagne for the seafood tower.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Seared Scallops': 'Tours-sur-Marne Pinot Noir rosé Champagne — benchmark rosé, silky mousse, red berry notes, long elegant finish. The strawberry-raspberry complexity frames scallops\' clean-seared sweetness and the fine bubbles refresh the browned edge. Peak rosé Champagne for scallops — elegance-on-elegance pairing.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|Shrimp Cocktail': 'Pinot Noir Champagne rosé from Tours-sur-Marne — silky mousse with strawberry, raspberry, and cherry. The red-berry profile cuts chilled shrimp\'s sweet brine and the long elegant finish plays against cocktail-sauce bite. Peak rosé Champagne for shrimp cocktail — benchmark starter pairing.',
  'Laurent Perrier Brut Rosé|The Tomahawk': 'Silky Pinot Noir rosé Champagne against the biggest marbled steak on the menu — the Tomahawk\'s rendered fat and char crushes the rosé\'s delicate strawberry-raspberry structure. Never pair. Route Tomahawk to Caymus, Opus, or Barolo and save the rosé for starters.',
  'Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut|Asparagus': 'Tours-sur-Marne Chardonnay-blend Champagne — precise green apple, lemon zest, whisper of brioche, vibrant acidity. The high-acid finish cuts through asparagus\'s sulfur edge and the brioche plays against the vegetal char. Works as Champagne for asparagus — bubbles on the wine-tricky vegetable; Sauv Blancs and Sancerre peak higher on sulfur notes.',
  'Laurent Perrier Le Cuvée Brut|Beignets': 'Tours-sur-Marne Chardonnay-blend Champagne — precise green apple, lemon zest, whisper of brioche, vibrant acidity. The high-acid finish cuts beignets\' fried-dough weight and the brioche complements the pastry directly. Strong elegant Champagne-with-dessert pairing — bubbles reset the palate at the sweet course.',
