  'Le Ragnaie Brunello|Au Gratin Potatoes': 'Tuscany Brunello di Montalcino DOCG Sangiovese Grosso — Le Ragnaie, five years minimum aging, dried cherry, tobacco, leather, rose petal, firm tannin, high acid. The high acid cuts gruyère-cream weight and the tobacco plays against the lactic richness. Works as Italy\'s-most-prestigious for au gratin — Brunello on the cheesy side.',
