  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Cowboy Ribeye': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, spice, medium body, low tannin. The refined structure underserves the big marbled ribeye — Pinot\'s low tannin falls short of the cut\'s fat-and-char demand. Works when guest wants lighter red with ribeye; Cabs peak higher.',
  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Crab Cake': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, spice, refined structure, low tannin. The soft tannin doesn\'t fight crab\'s sweet meat and the forest-floor earth plays against remoulade. Peak by-the-glass Pinot for crab cake — unconventional red that works where heavier reds would bury the shellfish.',
