  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Faroe Island Salmon': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, spice, refined structure. The elegant body plays against salmon\'s oil-rich flesh; preparation changes seasonally — check with kitchen for today\'s build. Strong by-the-glass Pinot for salmon — textbook Oregon-Pinot-with-salmon pairing across most preparations.',
  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Filet Mignon': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, whisper of spice, refined structure, medium body, low tannin. The elegant body meets butter-tender filet\'s lean sweetness and the forest-floor note plays against escargot-butter toppers. Peak by-the-glass Oregon Pinot for filet — accessible serious Pinot for the delicate cut.',
