  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|House Wedge': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, spice, refined structure. The low tannin and high acid cut iceberg-and-bacon and the dark cherry plays against blue cheese dressing. Peak by-the-glass Pinot for the wedge — Oregon elegance reframes the classic steakhouse salad.',
  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Kansas City': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, whisper of spice. The medium body works against Kansas City\'s lean-bold marbled strip though the low tannin falls short of the char-requirement of bolder Cabs. Strong by-the-glass Pinot for a guest wanting lighter red with the strip.',
  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Loaded Potato': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts the soup\'s bacon-cheddar weight and the forest-floor earth plays against the loaded toppings. Peaks from the dish\'s side; on this wine\'s card it\'s strong — below peaks with duck, lamb, and mushroom-sauced proteins. Confident pour when a guest anchors on Loaded Potato.',
  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Mushroom Bisque': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The forest-floor earth meshes directly with mushroom umami and the silky body lifts the cream base. Peaks from the dish\'s side; on this wine\'s card it\'s strong — below peaks with duck, lamb, and mushroom-sauced proteins. Confident pour when a guest anchors on Mushroom Bisque.',
  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Prime Tartare': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, whisper of spice, medium body. The low tannin leaves room for raw-beef delicacy and the cherry-forest-floor plays against egg yolk and capers. Peak by-the-glass Pinot for tartare — textbook red-with-raw-beef without overwhelming the dish.',
  'Lingua Franca Avni Pinot Noir|Rainbow Trout': 'Willamette Pinot — dark cherry, forest floor, refined structure, low tannin. The low-tannin silk lifts trout\'s delicate flesh but even the lightest red reads heavier than freshwater fish demands. Works as Oregon Pinot for rainbow trout — acceptable red; crisp whites peak higher on the delicate classic.',
