  'Pio Cesare Barbaresco|Porterhouse': 'Piedmont Barbaresco DOCG Nebbiolo — Pio Cesare Barolo\'s approachable sibling, floral aromatics, dried cherry, tar, firm-but-elegant tannins, full body, high acid. The firm-but-elegant tannin handles Porterhouse\'s dual strip-and-filet and the floral aromatics play against both lean-and-fatty sides. Strong approachable-Barolo-sibling for Porterhouse — Barbaresco elegance on the dual-cut.',
