  'Pio Cesare Barbaresco|Shrimp Cocktail': 'Approachable-Barolo-sibling Barbaresco against cold raw shrimp with horseradish — firm-tannin Pio Cesare and chilled shellfish with cocktail sauce is textbook clash. Never pair. Route shrimp cocktail to Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, Rosé, or Champagne; keep Pio Cesare for the steak course.',
  'Pio Cesare Barbaresco|Truffle Fries': 'Piedmont Barbaresco DOCG Nebbiolo — Pio Cesare Barolo\'s approachable sibling, floral aromatics, dried cherry, tar, firm-but-elegant tannins, high acid. The firm tannin cuts truffle-fry potato fat and the tar plays against the truffle-oil umami. Peak approachable-Barolo-sibling for truffle fries — tar-truffle echo on the umami hit.',
  'Poderi Aldo Conterno Nebbiolo|Au Gratin Potatoes': 'Piedmont Barolo DOCG Nebbiolo — Aldo Conterno Bussia Monforte d\'Alba, rose petal, tar, dried cherry, orange peel, iron minerality, firm tannin, high acid. The high acid cuts gruyère-cream weight and the tar plays against the lactic richness. Works as serious-Barolo for au gratin — Aldo Conterno prestige on the cheesy side.',
